* {{citation |last=Hobson |first=Benjamin |display-authors=0 |title=''《古訓撮要》 [''Gǔxùn Cuōyāo'' or ''Koo Huen Tsuy Yaou, Important Extracts from Ancient Authors'']'' |location=Guangzhou |date=1856 }}. {{zh icon}}
* {{citation |last=Hobson |first=Benjamin |display-authors=0 |title=''《基督降世傳》 [''Jīdū Jiàngshì Chuán'' or ''Ke Tuh Këang She Chuen, Advent of Christ'']'' |location=Guangzhou }}. {{zh icon}}
* {{citation |last=Hobson |first=Benjamin |display-authors=0 |title=''《聖地不收貪骨論》 [''Shèngdì Bù Shōu Tāngǔ Lún'' or ''Shing T'e Puh Show T'an Kuh Lun, Covetousness Excluded from Heaven'']'' |location=Guangzhou }}. {{zh icon}}
* {{citation |last=Hobson |first=Benjamin |display-authors=0 |title=''《聖主耶穌啓示聖差保羅復活之理》 [''Shèngzhǔ Yēsū Qǐshì Shèng Chā Bǎoluó Fùhuó zhī Lǐ'' or ''Shing Choo Yay Soo K'e She Shing Chae Paou Lo Fuh Hwo Che Le, The Doctrine of the Resurrection as Revealed to Paul by the Lord Jesus'']'' |location=Guangzhou }}. {{zh icon}}
* {{citation |last=Hobson |first=Benjamin |display-authors=0 |title=''《詩篇》 [''Shīpiān'' or ''She Pëen, Hymns'']'' |location=Guangzhou }}. {{zh icon}}
* {{citation |last=Hobson |first=Benjamin |display-authors=0 |title=''《論仁愛之要》 [''Lún Rénài zhī Yāo'' or ''Lun Jin Gae Che Yaou, The Importance of Love'']'' |location=Guangzhou }}, {{zh icon}} including translations of some New Testament chapters
* {{citation |last=Hobson |first=Benjamin |display-authors=0 |title=Annual Reports for Nine Years of the Missionary Hospital at Canton |date=1857 |location=Shanghai }}.
* {{citation |last=Hobson |first=Benjamin |display-authors=0 |title=''《西醫略論》 [''Xīyī Lüèlún'' or ''Se E Lëo Lun, First Lines on the Practice of Surgery in the West'']'' |location=Shanghai |date=1857 }}. {{zh icon}}
* {{citation |last=Hobson |first=Benjamin |display-authors=0 |title=A Medical Vocabulary in English and Chinese|date=1858 |location=Shanghai }}. {{en icon}}{{nbsp}}& {{zh icon}}
* {{citation |last=Hobson |first=Benjamin |display-authors=0 |title=''《婦婴新説》 [''Fùyīng Xīnshuō'' or ''Foo Ying Sin Shwo, Treatise on Midwifery and Diseases of Children'']'' |location=Shanghai |date=1858 }}. {{zh icon}}
* {{citation |last=Hobson |first=Benjamin |display-authors=0 |title=''《内科新誡》 [''Nèikē Xīnjiè'' or ''Nuy K'o Sin Shwo,<!--sic--> Practice of Medicine and Materia Medica'']'' |location=Shanghai |date=1858 }}. {{zh icon}}
* {{citation |last=Hobson |first=Benjamin |display-authors=0 |contribution=Dr. Hobson's Reports of the Hospitals at Macao and Hongkong |title=[[Chinese Repository]] |volume=Vols. 10, 11, 13, & 17 }}.

Five of the medical works were published with assistance from Kuan Mao-tsai. The illustrations of his ''Treatise on Physiology'' were derived from [[William Cheselden]]'s 1730 ''Anatomical Tables'' and 1733 ''Osteographia''.<ref name=taiduo/> Hobson's work has been called "instrumental" in introducing Western anatomical knowledge to China and [[Tokugawa Japan|Japan]], beginning their shift away from [[Traditional Chinese Medicine|traditional understandings]] based on the flow of ''[[qi (force)|qi]]'' and other [[pseudoscience]].<ref name=taiduo>{{cite journal |last1=Bosmia |first1=Anand N. |display-authors=1 |last2=Patel |first2=Toral R. |last3=Watanabe |first3=Koichi |last4=Shoja |first4=Mohammadali M. |last5=Loukas |first5=Marios |last6=Tubbs |first6=R. Shane |title=Benjamin Hobson (1816–1873): His Work as a Medical Missionary and Influence on the Practice of Medicine and Knowledge of Anatomy in China and Japan |journal=Clinical Anatomy |volume= 27|issue= 2 |pages=154–61 |year=2014 |pmid=23553744 |doi=10.1002/ca.22230 }}</ref>

