In [[Islamic]] context, '''Ghafara (غفر)''' (v. past tense) or '''maghfira''' (''forgiveness'') is one of three ways of [[forgiveness]], as written in the [[Qur'an]] and one of [[Allah]]'s characteristics. It is to forgive, to cover up ([[sins]]) and to [[remittance|remit]] ([[absolution]]).
