==Biography==
Saubhagyasagar was promoted as ''[[Acharya (Jainism)|Acharya]]'' in [[Karol Bagh]], [[Delhi]] in November 2014.<ref>{{citation |title=सौभाग्य सागर को मिला आचार्य पद |url=http://www.bhaskar.com/news/CHH-RAI-MAT-latest-raipur-news-025002-846736-NOR.html |work=[[Dainik Bhaskar]] |date=14 November 2014 }}</ref> He visited [[Etawah]], [[Uttar Pradesh]] in April 2016 and laid the foundation stone for "Mahamrityunjay Tirtha Kshetra".<ref>{{citation |title=सौभाग्य सागर आज रखेगे महामृत्युजंय तीर्थ क्षेत्र की आधार शिला |url=http://etawahlive.in/details1/2/%E0%A4%96%E0%A4%AC%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%82/2436 |work=[[Etawah Live]] |date=10 April 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{citation |title=आचार्य सौभाग्य सागर का हुआ नगर में मंगल प्रवेश |url=http://etawahlive.in/details1/2/%E0%A4%96%E0%A4%AC%E0%A4%B0%E0%A5%87%E0%A4%82/2515 |work=[[Etawah Live]] |date=17 April 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{citation |title=आचार्य सौभाग्य सागर का नगर में मंगल प्रवेश |url=http://www.jagran.com/uttar-pradesh/etawah-13882035.html |work=[[Dainik Jagran]] |date=17 April 2016 }}</ref>

